<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="86735" type="diagnosis and remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="86735">Diagnosis and remarks</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="86735">
This species was well described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Qian, Y. H." journalOrPublisher="Entomotaxonomia" pageId="0" pageNumber="86735" pagination="17 - 21" refId="B7866982" refString="Qian, Y. H., Du, Y. Z., 2012. Two new species of the genus Rhopalopsole (Plecoptera: Leuctridae) from China. Entomotaxonomia 34 (1): 17 - 21" title="Two new species of the genus Rhopalopsole (Plecoptera: Leuctridae) from China" volume="34" year="2012">Qian and Du (2012a)</bibRefCitation>
. Additionally, we found long hairs on the antennae (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F8002476" captionText="Figure 5. Male antennae, dorsal view. A Rhopalopsole intonsa Qian &amp; Du, 2012; B Rhopalopsole sinensis Yang &amp; Yang, 1993; C Rhopalopsole ampulla Du &amp; Qian, 2011; D Rhopalopsole exiguspina Du &amp; Qian, 2011; E Rhopalopsole memorabilis Qian &amp; Du, 2012." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e86735.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/711849" pageId="0" pageNumber="86735">5</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F8002480" captionText="Figure 6. Rhopalopsole intonsa Qian &amp; Du, 2012. A Male head and pronotum, dorsal view; B Male terminalia, dorsal view; C Male terminalia, lateral view; D Male terminalia, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e86735.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/711850" pageId="0" pageNumber="86735">6</figureCitation>
), which are only found in 
<taxonomicName genus="R." lsidName="R. sinensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="86735" rank="species" species="sinensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="86735">R. sinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Yang &amp; Yang, 1993, 
<taxonomicName genus="R." lsidName="R. ampulla" pageId="0" pageNumber="86735" rank="species" species="ampulla">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="86735">R. ampulla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Du &amp; Qian, 2011, 
<taxonomicName genus="R." lsidName="R. exiguspina" pageId="0" pageNumber="86735" rank="species" species="exiguspina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="86735">R. exiguspina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Du &amp; Qian, 2011 and 
<taxonomicName genus="R." lsidName="R. memorabilis" pageId="0" pageNumber="86735" rank="species" species="memorabilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="86735">R. memorabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Qian &amp; Du, 2012 in this genus. In this paper, we show the new images of the species to facilitate terminalia identification (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F8002480" captionText="Figure 6. Rhopalopsole intonsa Qian &amp; Du, 2012. A Male head and pronotum, dorsal view; B Male terminalia, dorsal view; C Male terminalia, lateral view; D Male terminalia, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e86735.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/711850" pageId="0" pageNumber="86735">6</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
